<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,781,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">
The structure of the mature larva of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[710,874,781,806]" class="Insecta" family="Platypezidae" genus="Lindneromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[710,874,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Lindneromyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1803" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[1095,1385,781,807]" class="Insecta" family="Platypezidae" genus="Platypeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1095,1211,781,806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Platypeza</emphasis>
Meigen, 
<number box="[1326,1385,781,807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1803.0">1803</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kessel &amp; Maggioncalda, 1968" authorityName="Kessel &amp; Maggioncalda" authorityYear="1968" box="[151,687,821,847]" class="Insecta" family="Platypezidae" genus="Paraplatypeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,322,821,846]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="60">Paraplatypeza</emphasis>
Kessel &amp; Maggioncalda, 
<number box="[626,687,821,847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="1968.0">1968</number>
</taxonomicName>
, but it has only the median pair of dorsal processes on each segment. The puparium is formed from the cuticle of the last larval instar and thus bears all larval cuticular structures. The length and maximum width of puparia are very similar to mature larvae. Numbering of segments follows 
<bibRefCitation author="Chandler" box="[253,457,941,967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" refString="Chandler, P. J. (2001) The flat-footed flies (Diptera: Opetiidae, Platypezidae) of Europe. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, Vol. 36. Brill, Leiden: Boston: Koln, 276 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Chandler (
<number box="[383,447,941,967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
: No. 
<number box="[532,576,941,967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
(sg 
<number box="[628,670,941,967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
) thoracic segments (pro-, meso-, metathorax), 
<number box="[1261,1319,941,967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="7.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="4.0">4–11</number>
(sg 
<number box="[1368,1428,941,967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" value="7.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="4.0">4–11</number>
) abdominal segments.
</paragraph>
